I get all you slash and thrust mercs out there, and your 50 50 30/31/32 spec, a 5th grader could understand that.  What Im wondering is this: A merc in some off chance may actually wanna go crush at higher lvls and just train slash till 40 and let crush auto, so he too could become a 50 50 30 merc.  But wait, crush doesnt auto, I just wanna know why.  Is it that hard to understand what Im asking<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#000000>(9/7/03 10:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> Well, firstly, for the &quot;Train &lt;Skill line&gt; to 40, and respec to get the extra points&quot; thing to work, you need at least one of the three damage lines to be a non auto-train, so in the end it can be dropped to 1, to get all your points back. Or else, all you'd be doing is swaping from one line ot the next, with no change.<br>
<br>
And, as i said before, &quot;Why does Crush not auto-train? You'd have to ask Mythic.&quot;. Mythic has a way of making some very strange choises sometimes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#000000>(9/8/03 3:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> I understand Iria on this.  I'm a Thrust Merc, always been a Thrust Merc.  Yet, my Slash has autotrained to +12 or whatever it is.  See the point she's making?<br>
<br>
So, I could respec out of Thrust and gain the autotrain points by going into Slash.  Yet I didn't train Crush to do it.<br>
<br>
So why can't you train Slash, then respec into Crush for the extra points?  Why is Crush omited for auto training? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dzeiger2>dzeiger2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#000000>(9/8/03 3:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> Either I'm misreading, or you are misunderstanding how auto-training and &quot;extra&quot; points work.<br>
<br>
If you are thrust spec, you cannot switch to slash and gain extra points?  Why?  Because thrust autotrains as well.  As a result, when you respec, the respec deducts the points necessary to keep thrust at the autotrain level (level 12 if you're 50).  As a result, by switching to slash, you gain nothing.  In fact, you would lose points switching from thrust to crush.<br>
<br>
The effect of adding auto-train to crush would be that nobody could ever gain the &quot;extra&quot; points again. <p>Acus TwinHammer<br>
50 Crush Merc, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 2:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> When  you do a /respec Thrust, you get back all your training points, minus the autotrain (in the case where someone has already done a Crush -&gt; respec Thrust.  Except, you don't get back the autotrain points from the /respec.<br>
<br>
Lets say I train Crush to lvl 50 as I level, then single respec into Slash.  I now have extra points because Slash autotrained.  I go to Sidi and I get a single line respec.<br>
<br>
I use that single line respec, get all my points I spent into Slash back, minus the points that were free from Autotrain.<br>
<br>
I now go to train into Thrust, which is already at +12 (or whatever it is). <br>
<br>
Do I not get the extra points because Thrust was already autotrained? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 2:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> Is this confusion caused by the difference between a Single Line Respec, and a Full Respec?<br>
<br>
If you use a Full Respec, it strips training from all your weapon types, so any Autotrain gets wiped as well.  But as far as I know, a single line respec shouldn't do that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crushmerc>crushmerc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 1:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> two posts up, about training from crush to slash to thrust.<br>
<br>
Okay we get crush to 50, slash and thrust have autotrained to 12. Let's say we go cookie cutter and put the remaining points into 50 DW and 28 parry.<br>
<br>
So, you get a single line respec and empty out Crush. You dump your points into slash, which is already at 12. Thus you gain 77 skill points to dump into whatever you want (probably parry). Your new spec would be 50 slash, 50 dw, 31 parry.<br>
<br>
Now, if you get another respec, you can take slash back down to 12, and bring thrust up to 50. Thrust was already at 12 from autotraining so you'd be able to with a single line respec.<br>
<br>
Now, from here if you tried to respec back into crush, you'd be fubar cause you could only take thrust back down to 12, leaving you 77 skill points short of bringing crush to 50.<br>
<br>
for anyone that trains in slash or thrust from the start and at 50 decides to respec to crush, it leaves them in a position of where they can only lower slash or thrust to 12. So they aren't able to bring crush all the way up.<br>
<br>
If Mythic decided to make crush autotrain, it would make it practically impossible... no, very difficult... well, more complicated to gain the additional skill points because they'd only be able to lower crush to 12.<br>
Those wishing to use crush at their end-game would benefit in that they would have the ability to gain the extra skill points and still use crush. However, in order to do this they would have to not train in any weapon type until it has fully autotrained. I guess they would just have to dump all their points into DW and parry. Maybe carry all three weapon types so they could use specific vs. armor type while they're in PvE. Use DW styles and maybe those of all three weapon types (the early ones you get til 12 ranks).<br>
<br>
Or get powerleveled.<br>
<br>
would be interesting if it ever happened, but personally I'm hoping more for shield equiped in the 2-hand slot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 1:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auto-Training Crush</span><hr size=1> It is impossible to train 50 DW/50 Crush/31 Parry.  That is what Iria is questioning.<br>
<br>
If you decide you're going to be a Crush Merc at lvl 50, and choose to level up using Slash, then why not let Crush Autotrain?<br>
<br>
Basically, whatever spec you choose to level up with, will never be autotrained because you're training it as you go.<br>
<br>
For example, I can level up with Slash, then respec and dump into Thrust to get 50 DW/50 Thrust/31 Parry.  When I respec out of Slash, it's back down to 1, not 12.  But I managed to &quot;autotrain&quot; Thrust without using the Crush spec.<br>
<br>
